      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "Azithromycin 1% ophthalmic solution was hypothesized to be efficacious in the treatment of CLDE because of results observed in preclinical studies involving inflammation and clinical studies in the subjects with anterior and/or posterior blepharitis. 27 Based on meeting the primary efficacy endpoint of the CFB in comfortable contact lens wear time, the results from this pilot study indicate that topical azithromycin 1% ophthalmic solution may be efficacious in treating subjects with CLDE."
